[resource]
script = ExtResource("3_dm202")
id = "manage_global_groups"
title = "Manage global groups for nodes"
description = "** Purpose **
Manage Global groups in the project.
Note: Groups are tags that can be set to nodes. Nodes can be added to a group without need to declare a Global group. Global groups are simply a quality-of-life feature that gives a handy dictionary of Group names to developers to avoid writing typos when setting a node's group in another scene.
  - Rule of thumb:
    - Create a Global group when a group can be used in many different scenes.
    - Don't create Global groups for groups that will be used in a single scene or in very few scenes.

** Usage notes **
- Send `action` Create or Delete.
- Send the desired `group_name`.
- Optionally send `group_description` if adding a new group. This is ignored for Delete action.

** Effect **
- The Godot project will be modified depending on the action. Note that the Godot UI will only reflect the change to the user, as a work-around they can move to another scene and come back.
- If adding a group that already exists, the description will be updated."
category = ExtResource("1_rtw56")
parameters = Array[ExtResource("2_c7fkw")]([SubResource("Resource_6oq01"), SubResource("Resource_jb0bt"), SubResource("Resource_pcgus"), ExtResource("5_d73fc")])
options = Array[ExtResource("1_26nfu")]([ExtResource("3_7svuf")])
